main event: Multiple unidentified objects were spotted on radar near Naha Air Base, Okinawa on August 30, 1961.
interesting points: About 12 objects appeared suddenly and increased in brightness next to a star.
The objects appeared to zigzag back and forth and exhibited changes in brightness.
The sighting was investigated by Captain Armand Teellecolette, who felt the incident was worth describing in detail.
Captain Teellecolette estimated the reliability of the observation as 7-8 out of 10.
No conclusion could be drawn from the information reported in the document.
